                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d770">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.93/383: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-22T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 22, 1937—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>363. A message from the Commander of the Yangtze Patrol indicates that Captain
                        Roberts<note n="37" xml:id="d770fn37">Capt. Frank N. Roberts, Assistant
                        Military Attaché in China.</note> will accompany you to Hankow.</p>
                <p>War Department desires to have Captain Roberts remain in Nanking with members of
                    Embassy staff whom you are leaving there unless you have cogent reasons for
                    taking him with you to Hankow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
